1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,160
The clatter of China against China, a familiar symphony in the Thornton household, usually

2
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:08,199
soothed a leaner.

3
00:00:08,199 --> 00:00:09,200
Not today.

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:15,759
Today, the sound was a grating reminder of her servitude, her gilded cage.

5
00:00:15,759 --> 00:00:20,120
She moved through the opulent dining room, clearing breakfast plates with a practiced

6
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:24,039
grace that belied the turmoil churning within.

7
00:00:24,039 --> 00:00:29,440
Sunlight streamed through the tall windows, illuminating dust-motes dancing in the air

8
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:35,320
and the obscene wealth on display the silver cutlery, the hand painted porcelain, the heavy

9
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,920
silk drapes.

10
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:43,520
Mr. Thornton, a man built like a brick wall and smelling faintly of expensive cigars and

11
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:46,799
ambition, hadn't touched his kippers.

12
00:00:46,799 --> 00:00:51,040
He sat hunched over the morning's newspaper, his brow furrowed.

13
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:56,520
Mrs. Thornton, a woman sculpted from ice and diamonds, picked delicately at a slice of

14
00:00:56,520 --> 00:01:02,560
melon, her gaze fixed on some distant, unattainable point.

15
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:07,840
Charles, their son, perpetually charming and utterly useless, was still a bed.

16
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:12,640
A leaner finished stacking the plates, her movements precise, almost robotic.

17
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:17,079
It was then she noticed at a crumpled piece of paper, half hidden beneath Mr. Thornton's

18
00:01:17,079 --> 00:01:19,040
discarded napkin.

19
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:24,840
It was an oddity, Mr. Thornton never discarded anything, and if he did, he ripped it up first.

20
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:30,159
Curiosity, a dangerous indulgence for a maid, nod at her.

21
00:01:30,159 --> 00:01:34,840
She lingered a moment longer than necessary, her heart hammering a frantic rhythm against

22
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,280
her ribs.

23
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:42,120
The Thornton's remained oblivious, lost in their separate worlds of privilege and entitlement.

24
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:46,439
Seizing her opportunity, a leaner subtly brushed the paper off the table and onto her

25
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:51,159
tray, concealing it beneath a stack of soiled linens.

26
00:01:51,159 --> 00:01:57,239
Back in the pantry, the scent of bleach and boiled vegetables filled the air.

27
00:01:57,239 --> 00:02:02,840
Mrs. Higgins, the cook, a woman with a heart as vast as her apron, was busy wrestling

28
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:05,039
with a stubborn goose.

29
00:02:05,039 --> 00:02:09,919
A leaner waited until Mrs. Higgins was safely engrossed before slipping the crumpled paper

30
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:12,079
into the pocket of her apron.

31
00:02:12,079 --> 00:02:16,000
The minutes crawled by, each task a torture.

32
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,879
Polishing silverware, dusting furniture, scrubbing floors all she could think about was the

33
00:02:20,879 --> 00:02:23,960
paper burning a hole in her pocket.

34
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:28,960
Finally, during her short break, she escaped to the cramped attic room she shared with

35
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,919
another maid, Mary.

36
00:02:30,919 --> 00:02:32,799
Mary was out, thank God.

37
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:35,960
A leaner bolted the door and unfolded the paper.

38
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:39,599
It was a bank statement, or rather, a photocopy of one.

39
00:02:39,599 --> 00:02:42,120
The name on the account wasn't Thornton.

40
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:45,240
It was associated agricultural initiatives.

41
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:50,240
A company a leaner had vaguely heard mentioned in whispers, linked to a controversial land

42
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,640
deal up north.

43
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:57,920
The figure that leaped out at her was the amount transferred, a staggering sum, larger than

44
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,360
anything a leaner could imagine.

45
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:05,480
The recipient, a name she didn't recognize, but the word bribes was scrawled beside it

46
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,719
in bold, angry letters.

47
00:03:07,719 --> 00:03:09,160
Her breath hitched.

48
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:14,360
Mr. Thornton, a man who lectured everyone on the virtues of honesty and hard work, was

49
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,920
implicated in something dirty.

50
00:03:16,919 --> 00:03:22,039
The news articles she'd read dismissed a sensationalist gossip suddenly clicked into

51
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:24,119
place.

52
00:03:24,119 --> 00:03:29,719
This land deal would displace dozens of families, forcing them off their ancestral farms.

53
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:32,879
Mr. Thornton, it seemed, was profiting from their misery.

54
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:35,319
A wave of nausea washed over her.

55
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:38,479
She knew Mr. Thornton, or at least she thought she did.

56
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:41,919
He was stern demanding, but never overtly cruel.

57
00:03:41,919 --> 00:03:46,439
He paid well by the standards of the time and provided steady employment.

58
00:03:46,439 --> 00:03:48,319
But this, this was different.

59
00:03:48,319 --> 00:03:52,319
This was a betrayal of everything she believed in.

60
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:57,879
Elyner had always been a quiet observer, a fly on the wall in this opulent world.

61
00:03:57,879 --> 00:04:03,159
She had seen the casual cruelty, the blatant disregard for those less fortunate, the insidious

62
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:05,599
ways in which wealth corrupted.

63
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:09,960
But she had always told herself it wasn't her place to judge that she was just a maid,

64
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,599
a cog in the machine.

65
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:17,439
Now the machine was spitting out in justice and she held the proof in her trembling hands.

66
00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:20,079
She had a choice to make.

67
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:23,079
She could ignore it pretend she hadn't seen anything.

68
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:26,279
Keep her head down, her job, her meager security.

69
00:04:26,279 --> 00:04:31,199
It was the safest option, the sensible option, but could she live with herself?

70
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:35,759
Could she continue to serve a man she knew was a cheat, a liar, a thief?

71
00:04:35,759 --> 00:04:40,399
The thought of those families their lives uprooted, their livelihoods destroyed, fueled

72
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:42,799
the flicker of defiance within her.

73
00:04:42,799 --> 00:04:46,079
Elyner wasn't a revolutionary.

74
00:04:46,079 --> 00:04:51,759
She was a simple girl raised on honest values who had never questioned the established order,

75
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:53,359
but this felt different.

76
00:04:53,359 --> 00:04:55,239
This felt wrong.

77
00:04:55,239 --> 00:04:56,599
Tears pricked at her eyes.

78
00:04:56,599 --> 00:04:58,000
She knew the risks.

79
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,959
Mr. Thornton was a powerful man.

80
00:04:59,959 --> 00:05:02,199
If she exposed him, he would crush her.

81
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,759
She would lose everything.

82
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:06,079
But what about the families he was crushing?

83
00:05:06,079 --> 00:05:07,560
What about her own conscience?

84
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:12,560
The weight of the decision pressed down on her, heavy and suffocating.

85
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,759
She paced the small room, her mind racing.

86
00:05:15,759 --> 00:05:19,680
There was Mrs. Higgins to think about who had treated Elyner like a daughter.

87
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:23,079
There was Mary, who relied on Elyner to share the rent.

88
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:26,199
Her actions would affect more than just herself.

89
00:05:26,199 --> 00:05:31,040
She looked around the cramped attic room at the Threadbare rug and the chipped wash basin

90
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:35,040
at the meager possessions that represented her entire world.

91
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,720
This was all she had.

92
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,160
Was it worth risking it all for a principle?

93
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:43,439
Suddenly a sharp wrap on the door startled her.

94
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:48,879
Elyner, Mrs. Thornton, wants you downstairs immediately, something about a missing broach.

95
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:50,040
Panic seized her.

96
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,720
Had she been gone too long?

97
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,680
Had someone noticed her absence?

98
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:57,960
She quickly folded the bank statement, shoving it back into her pocket.

99
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:04,040
Taking a deep breath, she plastered on her most subservient expression and opened the door.

100
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:08,920
Mrs. Thornton stood there, her face a mask of barely concealed impatience.

101
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,920
Where have you been, girl?

102
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,879
I've been looking all over for you.

103
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:15,600
My emerald broach is missing and I want you to help me find it.

104
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,000
Her voice was laced with suspicion.

105
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,879
Elyner felt a cold, dread creep into her bones.

106
00:06:20,879 --> 00:06:21,879
This was it.

107
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:23,879
This was the beginning of the end.

108
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:28,480
She followed Mrs. Thornton downstairs, her mind reeling.

109
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:33,439
The weight of the secret in her pocket felt heavier than ever before, a leaden burden

110
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:36,000
that threatened to drag her down.

111
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,079
The broach was found, of course.

112
00:06:38,079 --> 00:06:44,399
Tucked away in a drawer she cleaned only yesterday, but the suspicion remained.

113
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:48,240
The air in the Thornton household had subtly shifted.

114
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:52,480
Elyner was no longer invisible, a mere fixture in the background.

115
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,519
She was being watched.

116
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:59,720
That night, lying in bed beside a sleeping Mary, Elyner stared up at the ceiling, the

117
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:04,360
image of Mr. Thornton's face burned into her mind.

118
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,120
The decision had been made.

119
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,680
She couldn't remain silent.

120
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,240
She couldn't live with the lie.

121
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,240
But how?

122
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:15,400
How could she, a simple maid, possibly expose a man as powerful as Mr. Thornton?

123
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:20,280
The answer eluded her, shrouded in a fog of fear and uncertainty.

124
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:23,520
One thing was certain her life would never be the same.

125
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:28,640
The stain on the silk was spreading and she was about to be consumed by it.

126
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:33,839
The clatter of silverware against porcelain echoed, unnervingly loud in the Thornton's

127
00:07:33,839 --> 00:07:35,959
cavernous dining room.

128
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:41,000
Elyner kept her gaze fixed on the gravy boat she was meticulously refilling.

129
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,399
Her fingers trembling slightly.

130
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:48,680
Each movement was magnified under the watchful eyes of Mrs. Thornton, a woman whose presence

131
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,759
could curdle milk.

132
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:54,439
Rather clumsy today, aren't we, Elyner?

133
00:07:54,439 --> 00:07:58,680
Her voice, a low glacial drawl sliced through the air.

134
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:03,120
One would think working in service for so long would grant a degree of finesse.

135
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:06,639
Elyner flushed, fighting the urge to defend herself.

136
00:08:06,639 --> 00:08:09,439
My apologies, Madam, I'll be more careful.

137
00:08:09,439 --> 00:08:12,279
The lie tasted like ash in her mouth.

138
00:08:12,279 --> 00:08:13,759
Careful was her middle name.

139
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:18,879
She had to be navigating the treacherous currents of Thornton manner.

140
00:08:18,879 --> 00:08:23,399
The secret she carried, the knowledge of Mr. Thornton's fraudulent dealings in the

141
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:27,959
Docs redevelopment project, was a dangerous weight.

142
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:33,799
Every stolen glance at ledgers, every hushed conversation overheard was another brick in

143
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:38,480
the wall she was building against his carefully constructed empire.

144
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:43,439
But the higher the wall, the more precarious her position.

145
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:46,720
Mrs. Thornton's lips curled into a worthless smile.

146
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,000
See that you are.

147
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,199
This isn't some back alley kitchen, you know.

148
00:08:50,199 --> 00:08:52,759
This is a home built on excellence.

149
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:54,879
The hypocrisy stung.

150
00:08:54,879 --> 00:08:57,439
Excellence built on exploitation, Elyner thought.

151
00:08:57,439 --> 00:09:00,960
Her knuckles whitening as she gripped the gravy boat tighter.

152
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:05,399
Later that afternoon, while dusting the library, a voice startled her.

153
00:09:05,399 --> 00:09:08,399
Lost are we, Elyner?

154
00:09:08,399 --> 00:09:13,399
Charles Thornton leaned against a bookshelf, his usual charming smile in place.

155
00:09:13,399 --> 00:09:19,080
He was all easy charisma, a stark contrast to his mother's icy demeanor and his father's

156
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,679
ruthlessness.

157
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:23,319
Elyner's heart pounded against her ribs.

158
00:09:23,319 --> 00:09:29,759
He was another complication, another potential threat, just finishing my duties, Mr. Charles.

159
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:33,599
Duties duties, he sighed dramatically.

160
00:09:33,599 --> 00:09:36,439
Must life always be so regulated?

161
00:09:36,439 --> 00:09:40,120
Tell me Elyner, do you ever dream of escaping this gilded cage?

162
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:43,959
She paused her hand hovering over a leather-bound volume.

163
00:09:43,959 --> 00:09:46,079
Everyone dreams, Mr. Charles.

164
00:09:46,079 --> 00:09:49,519
And what are your dreams if I may be so bold as to ask?

165
00:09:49,519 --> 00:09:54,639
His eyes, a shade lighter than his father's, held an unsettling intensity.

166
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:59,559
She busied herself with the dusting, avoiding his gaze.

167
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:02,240
Dreams unsuitable for a maid, I imagine.

168
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,199
He chuckled, a low, seductive sound.

169
00:10:05,199 --> 00:10:06,919
Don't underestimate yourself, Elyner.

170
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:09,480
You possess a certain something, a spark.

171
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,439
It's rather captivating.

172
00:10:11,439 --> 00:10:14,759
He moved closer, invading her personal space.

173
00:10:14,759 --> 00:10:19,240
Perhaps we could explore those dreams together, away from the judging eyes of my esteemed

174
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,560
parents.

175
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:25,360
Elyner took a step back, her breath catching in her throat.

176
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,480
That would be inappropriate, Mr. Charles.

177
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,960
I must get back to my work.

178
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:34,440
She practically fled the library, his laughter echoing behind her.

179
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:37,399
Charles's interest was a double-edged sword.

180
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:42,399
It could offer her a degree of protection, a shield against his parents' suspicion.

181
00:10:42,399 --> 00:10:48,960
But it also made her a target, vulnerable to his whims and potential manipulations.

182
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:54,560
The evening, while sorting through Mr. Thornton's discarded papers, a risky habit she developed,

183
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:58,840
she found it, a letter slipped carelessly between documents.

184
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:04,680
It was from a solicitor, detailing a transaction involving a significant sum of money transferred

185
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:09,600
to an offshore account, a sum that directly correlated with the missing funds from the

186
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,759
Docs project.

187
00:11:11,759 --> 00:11:12,759
Evidence.

188
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:16,320
Solid, undeniable evidence.

189
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:18,640
Her heart leaped with a desperate hope.

190
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,720
This was it.

191
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:23,640
This was the key to unlocking the truth and exposing his corruption.

192
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:28,760
She carefully secreted the letter away, feeling a surge of exhilaration, but her triumph was

193
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,120
short-lived.

194
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,720
The next morning she was summoned to Mrs. Thornton's sitting room.

195
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:40,480
Elyner, she said, her voice laced with a chilling politeness, there seems to be a.

196
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:43,080
Descrepancy in the silver polishing.

197
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:48,480
Little pieces are missing their usual luster, and some, I dare say, are missing altogether.

198
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,639
Elyner's blood ran cold.

199
00:11:50,639 --> 00:11:52,600
She knew instantly what was happening.

200
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,120
This was a setup.

201
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:57,800
Madam, I assure you, I take great care with the silver.

202
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:01,120
Mrs. Thornton raised a perfectly sculpted eyebrow.

203
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:05,800
Indeed, perhaps a search of your quarters would be in order.

204
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:10,840
Just to be certain, two burly footmen entered the room, their faces grim.

205
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:13,720
Elyner felt a wave of nausea wash over her.

206
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:16,240
They already knew what they were going to find.

207
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:21,080
Within minutes, a silver locket, a small, insignificant piece from Mrs. Thornton's vast

208
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:25,680
collection, was discovered tucked away in Elyner's meager belongings.

209
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:29,160
I didn't I swear, I didn't take it.

210
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:32,519
Elyner cried, her voice cracking with despair.

211
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:35,639
Mrs. Thornton's smile was a thing of pure ice.

212
00:12:35,639 --> 00:12:36,879
Such a disappointment, Elyner.

213
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:41,720
I had such high hopes for you, but theft that is simply unacceptable.

214
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:47,320
The scene that followed was a blur of accusations, denials, and the cold, hard reality of her

215
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,720
situation.

216
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:55,080
She was publicly shamed, accused of betraying their trust and summarily dismissed.

217
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:59,799
Her belongings were unceremoniously dumped outside the servant's entrance, and she was

218
00:12:59,799 --> 00:13:04,919
left standing in the pouring rain, alone and utterly defeated.

219
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:09,839
As she walked away from Thornton's manner, her clothes soaked, her spirit broken, a figure

220
00:13:09,839 --> 00:13:11,879
emerged from the shadows.

221
00:13:11,879 --> 00:13:17,199
A woman, her face obscured by a wide, brimmed hat, approached her hesitantly.

222
00:13:17,199 --> 00:13:19,839
Are you, Elyner?

223
00:13:19,839 --> 00:13:22,839
The woman asked her voice trembling slightly.

224
00:13:22,839 --> 00:13:25,719
Elyner nodded, exhaustion weighing her down.

225
00:13:25,719 --> 00:13:27,240
I I heard what happened.

226
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:29,360
I've been wronged by Mr. Thornton, too.

227
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:33,199
He promised me things, and then he left me with nothing.

228
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,600
The woman's voice broke.

229
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,840
My name is Clara, and I think I think we need to talk.

230
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:44,040
Elyner stared at Clara, her mind-reeling, another victim, another betrayal.

231
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:48,400
The web of deceit surrounding Mr. Thornton seemed to stretch further than she could have ever

232
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,400
imagined.

233
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:53,640
Hope, fragile but persistent, flickered within her.

234
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,680
Perhaps together they could find a way to expose him.

235
00:13:56,680 --> 00:14:01,280
But as she looked into Clara's tear-filled eyes, a chilling thought occurred to her, could

236
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,800
she trust her?

237
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:08,719
Or was this just another carefully orchestrated move in Mr. Thornton's cruel game?

238
00:14:08,719 --> 00:14:14,959
The letter felt like a shard of glass in Elyner's hand, each crease a potential cut.

